The paper is about adapting Lucene, a search library, to operate within a serverless environment in the cloud. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category, which deals with search and retrieval of information. Additionally, the paper may also belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category, as it discusses operating within a cloud environment. The Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category may also be relevant, as the paper discusses adapting a search library to a new environment. The Database (cs.DB) sub-category may also be relevant, as the paper discusses a search library that is commonly used in database applications. Finally, the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category may be relevant, as the paper discusses a new implementation of a search library.
